// Shared build settings injected into Info.plist via $(...) expansion.
// Override per-config in Debug.xcconfig / Release.xcconfig / .env files.

// Base URL — point Debug at dev server, Release at shop-specific tenant URL.
BZ_API_BASE_URL = https://dev.bizarrecrm.com

// Comma-separated base64 SHA-256 hashes of server public keys (§1.2).
//
// Decision (2026-04-29): pins are LEFT EMPTY for bizarrecrm.com.
//
// Rationale:
//   • bizarrecrm.com uses Let's Encrypt certificates which rotate every 90 days.
//     Pinning to the leaf cert would require an app update every rotation cycle —
//     a reliability risk with no meaningful security gain for a known-CA chain.
//   • Pinning to Let's Encrypt intermediates (ISRG Root X1 / E5 / E6 / R10 / R11)
//     is feasible but Let's Encrypt periodically rotates intermediates too.
//   • Self-hosted tenants (custom domains, private CAs): populate BZ_SPKI_PINS
//     via a per-tenant Xcode configuration overlay or MDM profile, not here.
//     The `PinnedURLSessionDelegate` reads this key at runtime and enforces pins
//     only when the value is non-empty — zero cost for the hosted fleet.
//
// To enable for a specific build: set BZ_SPKI_PINS in the xcconfig for that
// target config, e.g.:
//   BZ_SPKI_PINS = sha256/AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=
BZ_SPKI_PINS =
